author: @sonalisamal2009
text: If this choreography isn't grand, royal, godly or majestic, then I don't know what is. I was closely observing everyone, even the supporting dancers, and what synchronisation they have! Being synchronised with 13 people is already a task in itself, but to be so consistent and do it so well with 200+ dancers is a big feat. So kudos to everyone involved. The supporting dancers looked like a machine being assembled. The way they were all walking away in complete unison and sync looked so disciplined. It was so smooth and free flowing. Everyone stood out in this song. The contrast between Mingyu and Joshua, and Hoshi/Dk and Jeonghan made it even better. The8's grand entry, Woozi being elevated, and everyone bowing down definitely felt regal. This was such a powerful choreography. Vocals were impactful. Seventeen is definitely one of the top groups out there. They prove it every now and then that they are indeed one of the best ❤

text:
## 안무 포인트 정리해봄... 진짜 세븐틴 안무영상 미쳤나봐요

0:18 웅장한 등장으로 시작
0:47 최고 중독성 파트 다룸다린다
1:13 센터의 진짜 아가 손오공과 함께 후렴 시작
1:27 I luv my Team I luv my Crew 가사, 박자, 춤, 에너지 모두 완벽
1:46 진짜 근두운 타고 날아가는 리더 
1:56 다룸다린다 늘어나라 하늘로 여의봉
2:10 진짜 숨참으면서 집중하게 되는 퍼포먼스팀 리더의 파워풀한 안무
2:24 흑화한 손오공 도사 포스 
2:41 댄서들 이끄는 메인보컬 보셨나요
2:55 속으로 What's That 외치면서 보는 파트..댄서분들도 너무 멋짐
3:08 핑부터 희열 오짐. 에네르기 궁쏘는 거 같음
3:20 만화책 넘기면서 '이 노래는 이 만화의 엔딩송' 미쳤나봄
3:30 댄서분들과 함께 분신술 안무.... 엔딩까지 너무 완벽

2. this time they used all instincts of their body to make EFFECTS of the video (revisiting MV to see why I said "they don't need special effects but special effects need them")

3. The domino ones are breathtaking 

4. Since the MV focuses on highlighting each member's solo part as well as the storyline via the setting and acting, the choreo vid made me more "thrilled" at how hard the choreo is :> now the cmt of Jun about the difficulty level of the choreo this comeback has been justified. I wonder when I would be able to cover it in full?????

5. How would they sing when dancing these moves????

author: @user-sunday
text:
아이돌과 댄스크루 합이 이렇게나 좋은 팀은 진짜 없다..
2:24 영상 효과 없는 거죠….? 사람 몸이 어떻게 버그를……..???
와 여운 진짜 대박이야…
세븐틴 데뷔부터 티비에 나올 때 가끔 본 게 전부지만 꾸준히 건강하고 대단한 그룹이란 걸 늘 느낌.
세대가 바뀌어서 요즘 아이돌성에 공감을 못하고 노래도 듣지 않는데 세븐틴은 종종 생각나서 들어오면 늘 새로운데 나 같은 사람,세대의 사람도 놀라고 감동하는 활동을 해줘서 마음이 울림. 저 수많은 사람들과 합을 맞추려면 얼마나 많은 노력을 할지 부터 한결같은 면이 있으면서도 자신과의 싸움에서 늘 이기는 듯 참신한 모습 보여주는데 팬들은 오죽 좋을까 싶음. 단순하고 반복적인 상업성이 아니라 이 팀만의 예술성이 느껴지고 자신들만의 예술을 고집하고 찾아가는 과정도 결과도 참 멋있다. 응원하는 그룹.

text: To describe the choreography as something impactful and neat is an understatement. No words could perfectly symbolize how beautiful the dance is and how satisfying it looks. I can only imagine how loud the chants will be as it echoes around the borders of every venue when they perform this song. SEVENTEEN never failed to showcase their passion and chemistry with everything that they do. Kudos to all the staff members, the CARATs who did not miss any opportunities to shower the boys with support and love, the production team, the dancers and choreographers, and lastly, to SEVENTEEN who made it this far and for being the strongest backbone of their own success. May not only this year, but also until how many years this family will stay together be surrounded with happiness and success.

author: @thenameless1896
text:
I think now they've truly gotten to the next level. The kings can now relax on their thrones and it shows. Let me explain: 
The reason why I love svt so much is that they're always striving for more, for something new and fresh, both musically and in their choreographies. 
Sure, they've had mega hits but even after those they didn't become complacent or tried to recreate the same success by creating something similar or based off the same mold. I think they truly are the hardest workers in the Kpop industry and with hard work come the difficulties and the stress... their strife for greatness also put a strain on them... 
I'm thinking about 2019 and hit especially...the song and choreography are awesome, but you can feel the tension. It's so physically hardcore that it's not sustainable in the long run (how they're still performing it at concerts it's a mystery to me). 
With 손오공 I feel like they've truly achieved greatness but in a more relaxed way (?)...there are 39 people performing that choreo, 39!! I think now they can truly enjoy their craft

author: @vindicatedtruth
text:
What SEVENTEEN is setting as a remarkable example for the industry is that just because you're a senior artist, doesn't mean you get to be complacent.  

Even after 8 years of achievements and accolades, SEVENTEEN refuses to rest on their laurels as they're determined to still pursue the perfectionism and passion of newly debuted rookies, the same hunger and fire for the stage never waning since their debut in 2015.

The only marked difference you can see in SEVENTEEN as senior artists is that their performances and music have much more finesse and elegance that only years of training and hard work have honed in them. 

SEVENTEEN have that same vitality even offstage too, bringing joy to Carats and Cubics and the larger general audience with their clever wit in various variety shows, refusing to be outdone by their younger contemporaries, even as their own self-produced idol variety show Going Seventeen has already made its mark as the Infinite Challenge of Kpop.

What sets SEVENTEEN apart is despite the fact that most senior artists by now have slowed down or eased off, SEVENTEEN instead pushes their standards higher and higher—in both performance AND entertainment—not only for themselves, but for the entire industry.

They're the standard to meet now. Not in awards and accolades, but in the respect they afford their job AND their fans through their sheer wholehearted commitment to their artistry.

They are, in every sense of the word, true leaders of the Kpop industry now, because they are telling their fellow idols:

Never back down, never settle, never let go.

Be like who SEVENTEEN are:

Be 손오공.

as expected, seventeen went all out again.

thank you for working hard to give has your 100% every comeback. i'm so proud of you, seventeen!

text:
For new carat's (Seventeens fandom) 
S.Coups: with white cap
Jeonghan: at the end sitting far left
Joshua: at the end standing obove Jeonghan
Jun: at the end standing next to Joshua
Hoshi: without cap, has untied shoelaces at the end (standing at the right side)
Wonwoo: at the end standing far right, next to Hoshi, wears only black with cap
Woozi: sitting in the beginning on the dancers shoulders
DK: at the end on the left side of the centre - standing person
Mingyu: at the end on the right side of the centre - standing person
The8: just dances a few parts with the others because of an injury at his arm
Seungkwan: at the end sitting far right
Vernon: at the end standing in the centre 
Dino: one with white/ blonde hair

I hope I could help. 
Seventeen is just the best group in K-Pop in my opinion.💎❤️
